# Drop your sysctl overrides here as <NN>-name.conf files.
#
# /etc/sysctl.d takes precedence over /usr/lib/sysctl.d (where cache22's
# defaults live), so anything you put here wins. systemd-sysctl.service
# applies them at every boot; run `sudo sysctl --system` to apply
# without rebooting.
#
# Files load lexicographically — a higher prefix overrides a lower one
# for the same key. The cache22 image ships:
#   /usr/lib/sysctl.d/60-cache22-network.conf      (BBR, fq, MTU probe)
#   /usr/lib/sysctl.d/70-cache22-containers.conf   (incus baseline)
#   /usr/lib/sysctl.d/80-cache22-server.conf       (server variant)
#   /usr/lib/sysctl.d/80-cache22-desktop.conf      (KDE variant)
